First, I would like to thank God for everything he has done in my life.  McNeese has given me so much to be thankful for — my life long friendships with coaches,  teammates, friends, an education, and most of all an opportunity. A chance to grow, learn, and create my own legacy. My freshman year changed my entire life when I lost my dad, but my family, friends, my team, and this school were always there with me. From the first day I left home I told my mom I would be legendary.  To the place that turned the kid into the Tiger, I am forever grateful.
